Dependencies:

[UBUNTU]
sudo apt-get install python-lxml python-django python-mutagen apache2 sqlite3 libapache2-mod-wsgi 




To get it running install laudio.tar.gz into /opt/ then insert the following command
sudo chmod -R a+r /opt/laudio

Extract the laudio-www to /var/www/ then insert the following command
sudo chmod -R a+rwx /var/www/laudio/

Add this at the end of the file to your /etc/apache2/httpd.conf:
sudo gedit /etc/apache2/httpd.conf

#####################################################################
#django and mod_wsgi conf
LoadModule wsgi_module               modules/mod_wsgi.so
Alias /laudio/media/ /var/www/laudio/
WSGIScriptAlias /laudio /var/www/laudio/django.wsgi

<Directory /opt/laudio>
Order allow,deny
Allow from all
</Directory>
#####################################################################

Now edit the settings.py
sudo gedit /opt/laudio/settings.py

and replace on line 5
WWW_PATH = ("/var/www/localhost/htdocs")

with
WWW_PATH = ("/var/www")

and finally a 
sudo /etc/init.d/apache2 restart
